<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">460.509/9–2151: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                        Indonesia</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-21T18:00:00-04:00">September 21, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>361. Fol in amplification first sentence <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 336 Sep 17<note n="1" xml:id="d413fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> “<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> exception
                                for <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> under Kem Amendment valid
                                without further renewal until Dec 30”. Admin required submit
                                Congress each quarter a review all exceptions made previously.
                                Exception granted <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Sep 13 must
                                be reviewed sometime during next quarter ending Dec 30 and decision
                                made whether continue exception.</p>
                            <p>Battle Bill in Cong conference to resolve differences in House and
                                Senate versions.<note n="2" xml:id="d413fn2">The reference is to the
                                    Mutual Defense Assistance Control Act, which became law on
                                    October 26, as Public Law 213. The text is printed in 65 Stat.
                                    644.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>